First unlike where Amazon pressed me to review  Bubble Guppies,  which I never bought,  Peppa Pig I actually bought and watch more actively with my daughter. There's jokes and incidental humor for both the kids and adults.
Unlike other kids shows this one I find novel in that there's a good mix of humor, lessons in manners and they actually have all the adults in the families actively involved with the things the children do, where in other shows it is as if adults don't exist or only the parents of the main character are shown. The brevity of the little shorts within the show also makes it easy to watch and enjoy.
